        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(browser): persist managed Chrome cookies across restarts",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Persist managed `openclaw` browser cookies via browser-level CDP `Storage.getCookies` / `Storage.setCookies`.\n- Restore the cookie sidecar on launch, flush it every 60s while Chrome runs, and snapshot once more before graceful stop.\n- Clear/delete the sidecar on a successful empty cookie snapshot so logout or cookie clearing is not undone later.\n- Clean up the periodic flush timer when managed Chrome exits/closes outside `stopOpenClawChrome`.\n- Add focused tests and document that the sidecar contains live login cookies.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\nManaged browser sessions can hold login cookies in Chrome's live CDP cookie store while the profile's SQLite cookie DB remains empty. When OpenClaw stops and relaunches the managed browser, those cookies disappear, so users lose authenticated browser state even when reusing the same managed profile.\n\nIssue #96704 has a live repro against current upstream `origin/main` showing a CDP-visible persistent cookie before restart, `0` rows in Chrome's cookie DB, and `0` cookies after relaunch with the same profile.\n\n## Security / Product Shape\nThis stores live browser login cookies in plaintext JSON at `~/.openclaw/browser/<profile>/cookies.json`, written `0600` beside the managed profile directory. That preserves login state across browser/gateway restarts, but it also duplicates sensitive browser state outside Chromium's own cookie DB.\n\nOpening this as a draft/RFC because maintainers may prefer default-on, opt-in, or a different persistence/encryption shape.\n\n## Evidence\n- Before-fix live repro against upstream main: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/96704#issuecomment-4848117522\n- After-fix live proof on branch head `4588b338bc3` using isolated temp gateway/browser ports `19984`/`20984` and temp profile `/private/tmp/openclaw-98284-proof-20260630/state/browser/openclaw/user-data`:\n  - Set synthetic persistent cookie `oc98284_after_fix` via browser-level CDP: `matchingCookies=1`.\n  - `openclaw browser stop` wrote `cookies.json` with `mode=600`, `cookieCount=1`, `hasProof=true`.\n  - Relaunched the same managed profile: `Storage.getCookies` returned `matchingCookies=1`.\n  - Cleared browser cookies via CDP: `totalCookies=0`; stopped the browser; `cookies.json` was absent.\n  - Relaunched the same managed profile again: `Storage.getCookies` returned `totalCookies=0`, `matchingCookies=0`.\n- Focused browser Vitest: `57/57` tests passed.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/browser/src/browser/cookie-persistence.test.ts extensions/browser/src/browser/chrome.test.ts`\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check docs/cli/browser.md extensions/browser/src/browser/chrome.ts extensions/browser/src/browser/chrome.test.ts extensions/browser/src/browser/cookie-persistence.ts extensions/browser/src/browser/cookie-persistence.test.ts`\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxlint docs/cli/browser.md extensions/browser/src/browser/chrome.ts extensions/browser/src/browser/chrome.test.ts extensions/browser/src/browser/cookie-persistence.ts extensions/browser/src/browser/cookie-persistence.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n\nFixes #96704\n",
        "branch": "codex/96704-browser-cookie-persistence",
